\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Project Title: Algorithmic Fairness Audit & Mitigation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Subtitle: Neutralizing Systemic Bias using AIF360 and Instance Reweighing\
1. Executive Summary (The "Why")\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This project demonstrates a technical pipeline for identifying and mitigating demographic bias in machine learning datasets. Using the 
\f0\b AI Fairness 360 (AIF360)
\f1\b0  toolkit, I audited a dataset with a pre-existing 60% success gap between genders. By applying 
\f0\b Instance Reweighing
\f1\b0 , I successfully neutralized the correlation between protected attributes and outcomes, achieving a 
\f0\b 1.0 Disparate Impact Ratio
\f1\b0  without removing critical features.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 2. The Technical Audit (The "How")\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 I structured this audit into three distinct phases: 
\f0\b Detection
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b Visualization
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b Intervention
\f1\b0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Phase A: Detection (Measuring the Gap)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 We first establish a baseline using the 
\f0\b Disparate Impact
\f1\b0  metric.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Initial Metric:
\f1\b0  0.2500\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Interpretation:
\f1\b0  This indicates that the unprivileged group is only 25% as likely to receive a positive outcome as the privileged group\'97well below the 0.80 regulatory "Four-Fifths" threshold.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 \strokec2 Phase B: Visualization (Profiling the Bias)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Before fixing the data, it is vital to profile it. I generated a success-rate distribution chart to visualize the 80/20 split between Males and Females.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Phase C: Intervention (The Mitigation)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 I utilized the 
\f0\b Reweighing
\f1\b0  algorithm. This is a "Pre-processing" technique that calculates weights for each individual in the training set to ensure the model treats both groups as mathematically equal.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 3. Code Summary & Explanation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Here is the core logic used in the audit, formatted for technical transparency:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Python\
\
# 1. DATA WRAPPING: Converting raw data into a 'Fairness-Aware' structure\
dataset = BinaryLabelDataset(df=df, label_names=['income'], protected_attribute_names=['gender'])\
\
# 2. CALCULATION: Identifying the 'Disparate Impact' baseline\
metric = BinaryLabelDatasetMetric(dataset, unprivileged_groups=unprivileged_groups, privileged_groups=privileged_groups)\
\
# 3. MITIGATION: Applying Reweighing to calculate 'Instance Weights'\
RW = Reweighing(unprivileged_groups=unprivileged_groups, privileged_groups=privileged_groups)\
dataset_transformed = RW.fit_transform(dataset)\
\
# 4. VERIFICATION: Confirming the new Disparate Impact is 1.0 (Perfect Fairness)\
metric_transformed = BinaryLabelDatasetMetric(dataset_transformed, ...)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
